  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[CRYING] I'm very frightened of the future, to the point where I thought twice that you know in the last minute about making this tape because I thought, what if the wrong people get this, and I don't want anything to happen to my kids.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[SOBBING] My husband, who is not religious, had the children baptized, you know, wanted them to be baptized Catholic at the time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[SOBBING] And he only told me years later that he did it because of his own fear, that something could happen.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[SOBBING] And he lived in a little village where there was-- I'm sure there was Anti-Semitism because there was when I returned there with him.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But when the Jews were marched there, he says that the villagers gave them food.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So [CRYING] people are of two-- two minds and two hearts.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You know, on the one hand they give food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And on the other hand, they disparage anybody that is not like them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
